==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Preter-
<hw>Pre"ter-</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L. <ets>praeter</ets> past,
beyond, originally a compar. of <ets>prae</ets> before. See
<er>For</er>, <ets>prep</ets>.]</ety> <def>A prefix signifying
<xex>past</xex>, <xex>by</xex>, <xex>beyond</xex>, <xex>more than</xex>;
<as>as, <ex>preter-</ex> mission, a permitting to go by;
<ex>preter</ex>natural, beyond or more than is natural.</as></def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>pr⟦ae⟧ter</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preterhuman</ent>⟦br⟧
